Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.23,0:00:09.73,main,Whitley,0,0,0,,Tee hee hee hee!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.29,0:00:12.48,main,Blake,0,0,0,,Do you really hate the Faunus that much?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.48,0:00:16.51,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,What a thing to say. The Faunus \Nare the ones who hate humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.51,0:00:20.12,main,Blake,0,0,0,,Not all Faunus are like that! \NHow many times do I have to say it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.12,0:00:22.00,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Blake, calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.42,0:00:25.25,main,Blake,0,0,0,,I'll distract her... \NI'll lure Negative Weiss away.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.25,0:00:26.00,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.00,0:00:29.18,main,Blake,0,0,0,,You and Yang go search for the Nightmare.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.18,0:00:31.13,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Uh, yeah. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.13,0:00:33.26,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,What are you whispering about?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.61,0:00:35.31,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,Step away from Ruby.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.31,0:00:38.51,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,I won't allow you to deceive \Nmy precious imperial subjects.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.51,0:00:40.14,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Precious?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.14,0:00:42.02,main,Blake,0,0,0,,The ones you locked in a tower?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.95,0:00:59.16,main,Whitley,0,0,0,,Tee hee hee!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.16,0:01:01.63,main,Whitley,0,0,0,,Look, she ran away, Sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.09,0:01:03.66,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,Silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.09,0:01:05.79,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,Klein, Sister...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.22,0:01:08.50,main,Dog Klein,0,0,0,,Achoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.22,0:01:14.17,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,Follow Ruby. I will take care of Blake.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.17,0:01:16.09,main,Commander Klein,0,0,0,,Aye-aye, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.60,0:01:27.48,Default,text,0,0,0,,{\fnTimes New Roman\b1\an8\c&HF0662B&\3c&HF0F3F1&\shad0}0
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.39,0:03:05.58,main,Yang,0,0,0,,It feels so weird to get \Nsleepy inside a dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.14,0:03:09.54,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Yang, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.54,0:03:11.30,main,Yang,0,0,0,,You're back! Where's Blake?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.30,0:03:14.40,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,She's distracting them. \NThe other Weiss is chasing her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.40,0:03:18.02,main,Yang,0,0,0,,And while she's doing that, we go \Nfind the Grimm possessing Weiss, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.02,0:03:20.12,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,How did you already know? Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.12,0:03:21.56,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Well, it just makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.45,0:03:28.44,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,I kinda don't feel like \NI'm pulling off this leader thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.83,0:03:30.44,main,Yang,0,0,0,,That isn't true at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.44,0:03:32.98,main,Yang,0,0,0,,But we don't have time for that anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.98,0:03:34.19,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Okay? Let's go, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.52,0:03:35.90,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.20,0:03:39.99,main,Sleepy Klein,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.99,0:03:43.41,main,Sleepy Klein,0,0,0,,I can hear Miss Ruby and Miss Yang's voices.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.41,0:03:45.61,main,Sleepy Klein,0,0,0,,What a relief, what a relief.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.93,0:03:52.36,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Oh. It really does seem \Nlike the inside of her heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.36,0:03:54.42,main,Yang,0,0,0,,So, where should we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.42,0:03:56.05,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,I wonder if we can use this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.54,0:04:10.46,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.46,0:04:12.93,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Right on! Nice job, Ruby!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.93,0:04:14.98,main,Yang,0,0,0,,You're the best! What a leader!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.28,0:04:16.43,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Tee hee.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.01,0:04:22.81,main,Commander Klein,0,0,0,,Ladies!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.81,0:04:27.50,main,Commander Klein,0,0,0,,As long as my eyes glow red, I, \NGrumpy Klein, will not let you pass!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.62,0:04:40.82,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,I have never known another \Nperson as outrageous as yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.82,0:04:44.61,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,I drive you out again and again, but you \Nkeep sneaking into my sacred places.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.61,0:04:47.56,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,Do you realize how much you've \Ndisturbed the sacred order?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.56,0:04:49.81,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,What an absolute nuisance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.81,0:04:52.51,main,Blake,0,0,0,,Are you that desperate to chase me away?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.51,0:04:55.57,main,Blake,0,0,0,,Or do you just hate being around Faunus?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.97,0:04:58.69,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,Faunus are not allowed to enter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.69,0:05:01.40,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,That is the law here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.25,0:05:08.46,main,Blake,0,0,0,,She doesn't run out of Dust?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.46,0:05:09.96,main,Blake,0,0,0,,I guess anything goes here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.96,0:05:13.59,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,I won't even wait for my sister \Nto pass judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.59,0:05:16.80,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,This time, I will finally \Nexpel you for eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.89,0:05:21.13,main,Blake,0,0,0,,Grimm? She can do that, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.15,0:05:31.53,main,Blake Decoy 1,0,0,0,,Are you that desperate to chase me away?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.53,0:05:33.44,main,Blake Decoy 1,0,0,0,,Are you that desperate to chase me—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.07,0:05:37.53,main,Blake Decoy 2,0,0,0,,Or do you just hate all Faunus? \NOr do you just hate all Faunus?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.89,0:05:48.16,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,And you always just run away!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.16,0:05:50.04,main,Whitley,0,0,0,,There's trouble, Sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.04,0:05:51.98,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,Don't bother me! Get back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.98,0:05:55.67,main,Whitley,0,0,0,,Even though I came all the way here to \Ntell you that Ruby and Yang escaped?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.67,0:05:57.63,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,What did you say? Yang, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.03,0:06:00.61,main,Whitley,0,0,0,,Blake sure took you for a ride!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.21,0:06:04.22,main,Whitley,0,0,0,,Don't forget your \Nresponsibilities, dear sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.88,0:06:10.80,main,Commander Klein,0,0,0,,I won't let you pass!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.35,0:06:16.45,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Oh, oops! It's this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.34,0:06:28.77,main,Commander Klein,0,0,0,,I am truly sorry, Mistress Weiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.77,0:06:30.13,main,Commander Klein,0,0,0,,Croak...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.13,0:06:32.83,main,Yang,0,0,0,,We're doing this for Weiss's sake!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.21,0:06:47.24,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Ew, it's pitch black.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.92,0:06:51.96,main,Yang,0,0,0,,This thorny briar patch \Nis a Grimm, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.42,0:06:55.79,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Please, take us to where Weiss is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.37,0:07:10.45,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,It worked!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.45,0:07:12.62,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Another success!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.90,0:07:15.00,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Hee-hee!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.21,0:07:20.48,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Huh? She's got Grimm, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.52,0:07:23.21,main,Yang,0,0,0,,What, are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.27,0:07:27.07,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah. We'll open a door.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.40,0:07:35.59,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Blake, so you fought that other Weiss?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.59,0:07:37.02,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Are you hurt or anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.02,0:07:39.02,main,Blake,0,0,0,,We were basically just playing tag.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.02,0:07:41.19,main,Blake,0,0,0,,But I'm fine. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.19,0:07:44.05,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Hey, how many coins do you have left?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.05,0:07:45.19,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,One left.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.49,0:07:47.57,main,Blake,0,0,0,,After all that, I'm also down to one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.95,0:07:49.45,main,Yang,0,0,0,,I have two.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.82,0:07:52.88,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Wanna pick who'll save the last one?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.88,0:07:54.53,main,Blake,0,0,0,,I'll leave it to our leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.53,0:07:57.83,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Um, okay, I'll save mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.29,0:07:59.96,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,I'll use it to get us out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.24,0:08:01.71,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Good, it's decided then.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.02,0:08:05.40,main,Yang,0,0,0,,If the Grimm is in there, \NI'll call the Professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.40,0:08:07.09,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Yeah, please do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.74,0:08:14.81,main,Blake,0,0,0,,The professor told us never to \Ntouch the Nightmare's thorns.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.81,0:08:17.78,main,Yang,0,0,0,,That would've been \Nimpossible without the relic.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.78,0:08:19.10,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Ruby had it covered.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.10,0:08:20.43,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Eheheh.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.70,0:08:24.65,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.86,0:08:24.35,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.86,0:08:24.35,main,Blake,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.88,0:08:34.60,main,Blake,0,0,0,,That's the Nightmare.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.79,0:08:36.69,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Yang.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.69,0:08:37.62,main,Yang,0,0,0,,I'm on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.00,0:08:46.55,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Ah, hello? This is Yang. Wha—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.55,0:08:47.58,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Sis?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.58,0:08:48.38,main,Yang,0,0,0,,What the?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.25,0:08:54.11,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,How dare you enter these sacred halls.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.81,0:09:06.48,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Wait, is she {\i1}protecting{\i0} the Grimm?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.48,0:09:10.34,main,Blake,0,0,0,,Do you really not understand why we're here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.34,0:09:12.45,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,Stop talking nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.75,0:09:14.43,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,Get out right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.45,0:09:21.50,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,The relic!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.47,0:09:27.50,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,Why betray me, Ruby?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.50,0:09:28.53,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.38,0:09:32.38,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,I must protect what is precious to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.82,0:09:35.51,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,Why can't you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.23,0:09:38.73,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Sorry, Weiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.23,0:09:41.36,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,I think I misunderstood.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.35,0:09:45.79,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,I don't really know... \Nwhat's precious to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.42,0:09:49.28,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,But there's no way it \Nwould be a Grimm, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.28,0:09:52.02,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,I'm begging you, open your eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.68,0:09:55.66,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,You've disappointed me, Yang.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.66,0:09:56.53,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.13,0:10:00.04,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,You're the one who made her like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.50,0:10:03.12,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,Spoiling her, coddling her...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.45,0:10:07.75,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,Your selfish behavior robbed \NRuby of the chance to grow up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.25,0:10:12.08,main,Yang,0,0,0,,You know, I'm starting to get, \Nlike, really ticked off!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.08,0:10:14.68,main,Yang,0,0,0,,You don't know what you're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.68,0:10:16.85,main,Blake,0,0,0,,Yang, no. Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.20,0:10:19.10,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,Enough of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.10,0:10:22.64,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,I'll lock the three of you away forever!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.12,0:10:32.82,main,Blake Decoy,0,0,0,,Calm down. Calm down. Calm down. Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.40,0:10:36.87,main,Yang Decoy,0,0,0,,Like, really ticked off! \NLike, really ticked off!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.72,0:10:40.73,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Ruby!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.12,0:10:44.12,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.37,0:10:46.21,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.51,0:10:53.84,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Why you...!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.01,0:11:01.06,main,Blake,0,0,0,,Yang!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.38,0:11:20.37,main,Shion,0,0,0,,Wake up now! Immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.94,0:11:35.01,main,Shion,0,0,0,,Phew. Did you all wake up?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.22,0:11:44.52,main,Shion,0,0,0,,I can sense that all of the markers \Nin the dream have been destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.52,0:11:48.90,main,Shion,0,0,0,,We have no choice but to enter \Nthe dream a third time and replace them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.90,0:11:50.96,main,Blake,0,0,0,,Starting again from scratch.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.09,0:11:57.95,main,Shion,0,0,0,,The landscape and the rules of Weiss's \Ndream should not change significantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.95,0:12:01.57,main,Shion,0,0,0,,Utilize what you have learned thus far \Nand devise a new strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.25,0:12:03.91,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,A strategy...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.22,0:12:07.97,main,Shion,0,0,0,,It will take some time \Nfor my Aura to recover.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.97,0:12:11.33,main,Shion,0,0,0,,Until then, the three of you\Nshould think about your plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.04,0:12:14.81,main,Shion,0,0,0,,If you do not succeed in the\N next attempt, however,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.87,0:12:17.91,main,Shion,0,0,0,,Weiss's life will be in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.64,0:12:31.06,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,I bet Weiss is hungry, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.06,0:12:34.89,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Jeez! What a selfish, \Nstubborn little princess.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.89,0:12:36.82,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Who does she think we're doing this for?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.12,0:12:40.40,main,Blake,0,0,0,,The Nightmare is just trying \Nto make us think she's like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.40,0:12:42.19,main,Blake,0,0,0,,Let's think about our plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.19,0:12:45.03,main,Blake,0,0,0,,Yang?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.03,0:12:46.83,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Where are you going, Sis?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.83,0:12:48.97,main,Yang,0,0,0,,To get some fresh air.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.97,0:12:51.69,main,Yang,0,0,0,,I can't fight when my mind's stuck on this,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.69,0:12:54.02,main,Yang,0,0,0,,so I won't be able to \Nthink of a strategy, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.02,0:12:57.17,main,Blake,0,0,0,,That's true. I'll do the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.17,0:12:59.73,main,Yang,0,0,0,,How about we meet back here in an hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.85,0:13:03.59,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Yeah. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.80,0:13:14.85,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,"Precious," she said...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.29,0:13:17.99,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Is that how she thinks about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.82,0:13:23.30,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,I want to understand her, \Nbut it's so hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.01,0:13:27.48,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Weiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.49,0:13:29.35,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.55,0:13:35.37,main,Sun,0,0,0,,What are you doin' all by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.28,0:13:38.31,main,Sun,0,0,0,,Shouldn't you be with your friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.97,0:13:47.72,flashback,Weiss,0,0,0,,You're just too soft on Ruby.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.09,0:13:50.97,flashback,Weiss,0,0,0,,My older sister was so strict...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.22,0:13:54.98,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Just shut up. I already knew that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.98,0:13:56.73,main,Penny,0,0,0,,What did you already know?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.95,0:13:58.25,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Woah! Where'd you come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.25,0:14:01.86,main,Penny,0,0,0,,Hello, my friend Ruby's older sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.86,0:14:03.90,main,Penny,0,0,0,,I am Penny.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.24,0:14:06.99,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah... Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.99,0:14:08.82,main,Penny,0,0,0,,Were you talking to yourself just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.82,0:14:13.13,main,Penny,0,0,0,,Or were you perhaps speaking with \Na being that is beyond my perception?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.13,0:14:14.81,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Talking to myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.81,0:14:19.03,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Or, more like talking to someone \Nfrom a dream. She's a little stubborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.75,0:14:22.25,main,Penny,0,0,0,,Then you may require maintenance.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.25,0:14:23.51,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Main...?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.87,0:14:29.51,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,There were versions of us \Ninside her dream, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.51,0:14:31.64,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,Huh. What were we like?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.64,0:14:34.39,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Uh, um, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.39,0:14:39.73,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Just like me, all of you are \Nlocked up somewhere in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.99,0:14:43.73,main,Nora,0,0,0,,Why, though? Did we ever \Ndo anything bad to Weiss?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.00,0:14:47.24,main,Ren,0,0,0,,We might not be locked up \Nbecause we're bad, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.24,0:14:48.07,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.24,0:14:48.07,main,Nora,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.42,0:14:49.45,main,Pyrrha,0,0,0,,He's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.45,0:14:50.86,main,Pyrrha,0,0,0,,When something is really important to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.86,0:14:52.83,main,Pyrrha,0,0,0,,don't you want to hide it \Naway and keep it safe?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.83,0:14:55.25,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,Because you're scared \Nof losing it or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.25,0:14:59.83,main,Pyrrha,0,0,0,,Right. Maybe she's trying to protect her \Nmemories of her friends from the Nightmare.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.58,0:15:06.34,main,Nora,0,0,0,,Aw, well at least let me out. \NThen we could fight together.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.73,0:15:08.72,main,Ren,0,0,0,,That really isn't the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.76,0:15:11.59,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Fight together...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.60,0:15:16.98,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,I wish I could, too. \NI can recover really quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.98,0:15:18.23,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.23,0:15:25.20,main,Penny,0,0,0,,I have learned that dreams are maintenance,\Nused to process excess information.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.20,0:15:27.80,main,Penny,0,0,0,,So I, too, make efforts to dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.80,0:15:31.48,main,Penny,0,0,0,,To this end, I have conceived and\Nprogrammed many different scenarios.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.48,0:15:34.24,main,Yang,0,0,0,,I... don't really understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.61,0:15:36.53,main,Penny,0,0,0,,It is possible to perform \Nvarious kinds of maintenance
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.53,0:15:38.88,main,Penny,0,0,0,,by swapping out different dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.88,0:15:41.88,main,Penny,0,0,0,,Why don't you try that too, \NRuby's older sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.64,0:15:44.25,main,Yang,0,0,0,,It's Yang.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.25,0:15:46.13,main,Yang,0,0,0,,That's not how it works...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.96,0:15:53.02,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Oh? Maintenance, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.64,0:16:01.64,main,Sun,0,0,0,,Huh. In the dream, \Nyour friend keeps you away?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.94,0:16:03.15,main,Blake,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.44,0:16:07.67,main,Blake,0,0,0,,The same way that human society \Nkeeps the Faunus at a distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.67,0:16:11.15,main,Sun,0,0,0,,But doesn't that just show how \Nmuch she's thinking about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.92,0:16:13.66,main,Blake,0,0,0,,Thinking about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.66,0:16:16.44,main,Sun,0,0,0,,In the dream, if she pushes you away \Nbut you keep coming back,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.44,0:16:17.93,main,Sun,0,0,0,,that's gotta be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.93,0:16:21.78,main,Sun,0,0,0,,I mean, I get the feeling \Nit means your being there
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.78,0:16:23.37,main,Sun,0,0,0,,is powerful enough to change her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.91,0:16:27.18,main,Blake,0,0,0,,Change... Weiss?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.15,0:16:29.32,main,Blake,0,0,0,,Can I?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.80,0:16:32.00,main,Sun,0,0,0,,If she's accepted you,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.00,0:16:34.80,main,Sun,0,0,0,,that's awesome in itself, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.80,0:16:38.56,main,Sun,0,0,0,,Doesn't it mean you were \Nable to change her mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.80,0:16:44.56,main,Blake,0,0,0,,The White Fang's founding ideals \Nwere like that too, at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.56,0:16:45.56,main,Sun,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.88,0:16:50.24,main,Blake,0,0,0,,We wanted to change the world. \NWe wanted them to accept us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.67,0:16:53.95,main,Blake,0,0,0,,But then after being rejected,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.23,0:16:55.91,main,Blake,0,0,0,,after losing hope,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.91,0:16:57.91,main,Blake,0,0,0,,violence was the only thing left for some.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.11,0:17:03.21,main,Blake,0,0,0,,But I refuse to lose hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.21,0:17:05.00,main,Blake,0,0,0,,No matter how many times I'm rejected,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.00,0:17:07.34,main,Blake,0,0,0,,I'll keep trying to make them accept us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.36,0:17:10.34,main,Blake,0,0,0,,Thanks, Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.67,0:17:15.87,main,Sun,0,0,0,,Believing that you can both \Nchange each other for the better...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.87,0:17:18.72,main,Sun,0,0,0,,Isn't that what friends are for?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.02,0:17:20.10,main,Sun,0,0,0,,Don't give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.07,0:17:29.50,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,...and then maybe Negative Weiss will \Nforget about protecting the Grimm.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.50,0:17:33.36,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Once Negative Weiss is gone, \Nwe'll totally be able to beat the Grimm.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.36,0:17:34.74,main,Pyrrha,0,0,0,,Certainly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.74,0:17:38.36,main,Pyrrha,0,0,0,,When we did it, more than \Nthe Nightmare itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.36,0:17:41.37,main,Pyrrha,0,0,0,,it felt like parts of Jaune's \Ndream were attacking us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.69,0:17:44.25,main,Nora,0,0,0,,That Grimm isn't that strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.64,0:17:47.50,main,Ren,0,0,0,,Well, at least it wasn't when we fought it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.31,0:17:51.88,main,Yang,0,0,0,,What's this? You're ironing \Nout a plan with Team JNPR?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.88,0:17:54.38,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Yeah. Welcome back, Sis.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.38,0:17:57.39,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Guess what! I came up with a strategy!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.39,0:17:58.36,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Heh.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.36,0:18:00.06,main,Yang,0,0,0,,And. So. Did. I!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.06,0:18:01.14,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Wanna hear it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.14,0:18:03.27,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Yeah! Tell me! Tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.27,0:18:05.63,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Once Blake gets here... Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.61,0:18:10.02,main,Blake,0,0,0,,Sorry I'm late.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.33,0:18:12.27,main,Yang,0,0,0,,I just got here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.27,0:18:13.90,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Did you think of something?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.21,0:18:17.57,main,Yang,0,0,0,,More like, I know what I need to do now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.57,0:18:20.07,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Then let's call a team meeting!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.72,0:18:26.46,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Well? What do you think of our plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.91,0:18:31.35,main,Shion,0,0,0,,First, regarding Yang's idea,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.35,0:18:34.61,main,Shion,0,0,0,,yes, it is possible to change \Nwhat happens in a dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.21,0:18:36.84,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.20,0:18:41.61,main,Ozpin,0,0,0,,But only if the dreamer \Nsees it as a positive change.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.17,0:18:46.60,main,Ozpin,0,0,0,,If Weiss considers it to be a negative change,\N you will encounter resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.37,0:18:52.66,main,Blake,0,0,0,,I feel like I understand \Nhow Weiss wants to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.66,0:18:54.41,main,Blake,0,0,0,,I was the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.41,0:18:58.56,main,Blake,0,0,0,,I knew I had to change, \Nbut I couldn't find a way to.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.03,0:19:03.90,main,Yang,0,0,0,,I want to tell Weiss, deep in \Nher heart, that it's okay to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.90,0:19:07.55,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,I'm sure that Weiss will also think \Nthat what we're about to do
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.55,0:19:10.27,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,is something good. I believe that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.95,0:19:14.81,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,I didn't understand,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.53,0:19:18.13,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,but we're not the only ones \Nwho are struggling.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.13,0:19:21.93,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Even Weiss is fighting \Nagainst the Grimm in her heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.14,0:19:25.78,main,Shion,0,0,0,,Very well. One last thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.14,0:19:30.28,main,Shion,0,0,0,,Regarding Ruby's idea, \Nit actually does have precedent,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.28,0:19:32.63,main,Shion,0,0,0,,and it has generally \Nproduced positive results.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.02,0:19:34.82,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.82,0:19:38.28,main,Pyrrha,0,0,0,,So prior experience with \NNightmare possession can be useful?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.28,0:19:39.53,main,Shion,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.17,0:19:45.20,main,Shion,0,0,0,,Jaune's heart still retains the memory \Nof hosting the parasitic Nightmare.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.20,0:19:49.61,main,Shion,0,0,0,,Other Nightmares will mistake Jaune \Nfor someone who is still possessed,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.61,0:19:51.29,main,Shion,0,0,0,,and will likely ignore him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.64,0:19:52.79,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Oh, no kidding?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.79,0:19:54.81,main,Nora,0,0,0,,You mean he's not worth noticing?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.81,0:19:56.42,main,Ren,0,0,0,,No, Nora.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.85,0:19:59.42,main,Shion,0,0,0,,He has developed immunity, so to speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.71,0:20:02.40,main,Shion,0,0,0,,But the closer Jaune gets \Nto the Nightmare's body,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.40,0:20:04.43,main,Shion,0,0,0,,the more of a reaction he'll have.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.43,0:20:06.83,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,Eh... What kind?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.83,0:20:12.10,main,Shion,0,0,0,,The most common ones are itching \Nand difficulty breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.10,0:20:14.15,main,Pyrrha,0,0,0,,That's just like an allergy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.15,0:20:16.15,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,I'm getting a bad feeling about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.62,0:20:20.01,main,Shion,0,0,0,,In return, you should be \Nable to move quite freely
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.01,0:20:22.38,main,Shion,0,0,0,,in a dream controlled by a Nightmare.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.38,0:20:24.04,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Seriously? That's great!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.04,0:20:26.25,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,We can totally use your help, Jaune!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.25,0:20:28.82,main,Shion,0,0,0,,But if the rejection is too strong,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.82,0:20:31.74,main,Shion,0,0,0,,there is a risk he may die \Nfrom shock inside the dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.67,0:20:34.04,main,Shion,0,0,0,,Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.04,0:20:36.04,main,Nora,0,0,0,,Ew. Dying in your sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.04,0:20:38.30,main,Ren,0,0,0,,Please stay alive, Jaune.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.30,0:20:41.67,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,Ugh... but this is for her sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.13,0:20:44.18,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,I hope I can pull it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.18,0:20:46.90,main,Pyrrha,0,0,0,,I know you can do it, Jaune.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.90,0:20:49.49,main,Pyrrha,0,0,0,,Believe in yourself and your Aura.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.49,0:20:50.90,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,I'll try.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.06,0:20:55.69,main,Shion,0,0,0,,You have to search for the key to her heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.33,0:20:59.40,main,Shion,0,0,0,,Somewhere in the dream, \Nthere should be an item
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.40,0:21:01.71,main,Shion,0,0,0,,identical to the one you found before.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.71,0:21:03.25,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,All right, Professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.83,0:21:07.86,main,Shion,0,0,0,,I do not mean to frighten you, \Nbut if you fail again,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.86,0:21:10.49,main,Shion,0,0,0,,in the time that it takes \Nfor my Aura to recover,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.49,0:21:13.05,main,Shion,0,0,0,,it is quite likely that Weiss \Nwill lose her life.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.17,0:21:15.53,main,Shion,0,0,0,,Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.53,0:21:17.46,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,We won't fail again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.46,0:21:20.49,main,Yang,0,0,0,,We gotta hurry and wake Weiss up,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.49,0:21:23.34,main,Yang,0,0,0,,so we can tell her how \Ntough this was, right guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.82,0:21:28.83,main,Blake,0,0,0,,Yeah. Right now, I just want to talk \Nto her. About all sorts of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.10,0:21:34.23,main,Shion,0,0,0,,All right, prepare to enter the dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.38,0:21:46.55,main,Shion,0,0,0,,I now invite you all into the dream.
